<div class="row">
	<div class="col-md-6">
		<div class="recipe-modal-img-container">
			<img src="${pageContext.request.contextPath}/recipes/Chicken_Tortilla_Soup.jpg" />
		</div>
		<h4>Ingredients</h4>
		<ul class="ingredients">
			<li>2 whole boneless, skinless chicken breasts</li>
			<li>2 Tbsp Olive Oil</li>
			<li>1 1/2 ts cumin</li>
			<li>1 tsp chili powder</li>
			<li>1/2 tsp garlic powder</li>
			<li>1/2 tsp salt</li>
			<li>1 cup diced onion</li>
			<li>1/2 cup diced green bell pepper</li>
			<li>1/4 cup diced red bell pepper</li>
			<li>1 small zucchini, chopped</li>
			<li>3 cloves garlic, minced</li>
			<li>1 can (10 oz) Rotel tomatoes</li>
			<li>32 ounces low sodium chicken stock</li>
			<li>3 Tbsp tomato paste</li>
			<li>3 cups hot water</li>
		</ul>
	</div>
	<div class="col-md-6">
		<h4>Instructions</h4>
		<ol class="instructions">
			<li>boil chicken in 2 cups water until cooked thoroughly. Shred chicken into smaller pieces after it has cooked and cooled.</li>
			<li>heat 1 Tbsp olive oil in a pot over medium-high heat. Add red pepper, green pepper, garlic, and zucchini. Stir and begin cooking, then add the rest of the spice mix. Stir to combine, then add shredded chicken and onions.</li>
			<li>pour in Rotel, chicken stock, tomato paste, and water. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to a simmer. Simmer for 30 minutes, uncovered.</li>
			<li>top with fresh pico de gallo or cilantro! Ideal Protein 'Salty Snacks' make great soup toppers as well, or get creative and make 'tortilla strips' with IP Pancake Mix!</li>
		</ol>
	</div>
</div>